<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>Is your app customer-ready? — Pre-Launch Checklist · LaunchLook</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:opsz,wght@9..144,500;9..144,600&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <style>
    :root {
      --paper: #FAF7F2;
      --ink: #1F1B16;
      --muted: #6B6359;
      --accent: {{ primary_color | default('#B45309') }};
      --line: #E7E0D6;
      --surface: #FFFFFF;
      --surface-tint: #F4EFE7;
    }

    @page {
      size: A4 portrait;
      margin: 22mm 18mm 20mm 18mm;
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; }

    html, body {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      background: var(--paper);
      color: var(--ink);
      font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
      font-size: 10pt;
      line-height: 1.55;
      -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;
      print-color-adjust: exact;
    }

    .doc-header {
      border-top: 3px solid var(--accent);
      padding-top: 9pt;
      margin-bottom: 12pt;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      font-size: 8pt;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--accent);
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin: 0;
    }

    h1 {
      font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
      font-weight: 500;
      font-size: 22pt;
      line-height: 1.15;
      margin: 5pt 0 3pt;
      color: var(--ink);
      letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    }

    .subtitle {
      font-size: 9.5pt;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin: 0;
    }

    .intro {
      margin: 12pt 0 14pt;
      padding: 11pt 14pt;
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
      border-radius: 4pt;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .intro p {
      margin: 0 0 6pt;
      font-size: 10pt;
      color: var(--ink);
    }

    .intro p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    h2 {
      font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
      font-weight: 500;
      font-size: 13pt;
      margin: 14pt 0 4pt;
      padding-bottom: 3pt;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
      page-break-after: avoid;
    }

    .section-meta {
      font-size: 8.5pt;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin: 0 0 6pt;
    }

    ul.checks {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      list-style: none;
    }

    ul.checks li {
      position: relative;
      padding: 3pt 0 3pt 20pt;
      font-size: 9.5pt;
      color: var(--ink);
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    ul.checks li::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      top: 5pt;
      left: 2pt;
      width: 10pt;
      height: 10pt;
      border: 1px solid var(--muted);
      border-radius: 2pt;
      background: var(--surface);
    }

    .next-block {
      margin-top: 14pt;
      padding: 11pt 14pt;
      background: var(--surface-tint);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 4pt;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .next-block h3 {
      font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
      font-weight: 500;
      font-size: 12pt;
      margin: 0 0 5pt;
    }

    .next-block ul {
      margin: 0;
      padding-left: 16pt;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 9.5pt;
    }

    .next-block ul li { margin-bottom: 3pt; }
    .next-block strong { color: var(--ink); }

    .closing {
      margin-top: 16pt;
      padding-top: 8pt;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
      font-size: 8.5pt;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .closing a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <header class="doc-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">
      LaunchLook · Pre-Launch Checklist
      {%- if customer and customer.tier %} · bundled with {{ customer.tier }}{% endif %}
    </p>
    <h1>Is your app customer-ready? &mdash; Pre-Launch Checklist</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      Work through this on your live site before you share the link · 30&ndash;45 minutes
      {%- if customer and customer.app_name %} · prepared for {{ customer.app_name }}{% endif %}
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="intro">
    <p>Work through this in order on your <strong>live site</strong> (not your editor preview). If you fail an item, fix it before moving on.</p>
    <p>LaunchLook checks many of these automatically as part of your audit &mdash; your job is to confirm each one is actually true on the live site.</p>
    <p>Total time: 30&ndash;45 minutes, plus the &ldquo;watch someone use it&rdquo; step at the end.</p>
  </section>

  <h2>1. First look</h2>
  <p class="section-meta">~5 min &middot; homepage and footer</p>
  <ul class="checks">
    <li>Live link loads quickly, no spinning.</li>
    <li>Padlock in URL bar (no &ldquo;Not Secure&rdquo; warning).</li>
    <li>Browser tab shows your app name and a real favicon &mdash; not a generic globe or builder default.</li>
    <li>A stranger can tell what the app does within a few seconds from the homepage alone.</li>
    <li>No placeholder text (lorem ipsum, &ldquo;Your Company Name,&rdquo; TODO notes).</li>
    <li>No default &ldquo;welcome to your new app&rdquo; builder copy.</li>
    <li>Your product name in the header, not the platform&rsquo;s logo.</li>
    <li>Nothing &ldquo;developer only&rdquo; visible (test buttons, skip-login, seed data).</li>
    <li>Main homepage button does what it promises.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Data hygiene</h2>
  <p class="section-meta">~3 min &middot; the most common pre-launch miss</p>
  <ul class="checks">
    <li>Test accounts, fake users, and seed data deleted (or clearly labelled &ldquo;Demo&rdquo;).</li>
    <li>No real names, emails, or photos from beta testers visible to new visitors.</li>
    <li>Your own admin/dev account isn&rsquo;t showing up in any public list.</li>
    <li>Any &ldquo;example&rdquo; content reads like real content a customer would expect to see.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Trust &amp; contact</h2>
  <p class="section-meta">~3 min</p>
  <ul class="checks">
    <li>/privacy page exists and describes what data you actually collect (not a blank template).</li>
    <li>/terms page exists and reflects your actual terms (not a blank template).</li>
    <li>Visitors can find how to reach you.</li>
    <li>That email is real and monitored &mdash; not support@example.com.</li>
    <li>Footer privacy/terms links work (no 404).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Does the main flow work?</h2>
  <p class="section-meta">~10 min</p>
  <ul class="checks">
    <li>Buttons and links do something &mdash; no dead ends.</li>
    <li>Signup confirmation email arrives within a minute (check spam too).</li>
    <li>Email from your app lands in the inbox, not spam.</li>
    <li>You can log in after signing up.</li>
    <li>You can log out.</li>
    <li>Contact and signup forms aren&rsquo;t getting flooded by spam submissions.</li>
    <li>Core workflow completes end-to-end (book, pay, submit, save).</li>
    <li>Form submission shows a clear success or failure message.</li>
    <li>Test payment completes with a sensible thank-you page.</li>
    <li>New user isn&rsquo;t staring at a blank screen with no guidance.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. When things go wrong</h2>
  <p class="section-meta">~5 min</p>
  <ul class="checks">
    <li>Wrong password shows a clear message, not a crash or generic error.</li>
    <li>A made-up URL (yoursite.com/asdf) shows a 404 page with a link back home.</li>
    <li>Refreshing mid-workflow doesn&rsquo;t wipe the user&rsquo;s progress without warning.</li>
    <li>Closing the tab and coming back: signed-in state behaves sensibly.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. On a phone</h2>
  <p class="section-meta">~5 min</p>
  <ul class="checks">
    <li>No sideways scrolling.</li>
    <li>Text readable without pinching to zoom.</li>
    <li>Buttons easy to tap, not tiny.</li>
    <li>Main workflow usable on phone, not only desktop.</li>
    <li>Email field shows the @ key, number fields show the number pad.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>7. Sharing your link</h2>
  <p class="section-meta">~2 min</p>
  <ul class="checks">
    <li>Paste URL into Slack, iMessage, or LinkedIn &mdash; preview shows the right title, description, and image, not builder default.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>8. If your app has user accounts</h2>
  <p class="section-meta">Required if applicable &middot; skip only if your app has no accounts at all</p>
  <ul class="checks">
    <li>Signed in as person A, you cannot see person B&rsquo;s private data.</li>
    <li>When signed out, protected pages ask you to log in instead of showing someone else&rsquo;s data.</li>
    <li>Password reset flow works end-to-end: request email, receive it, set new password, log in successfully.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>9. The real test</h2>
  <p class="section-meta">~10&ndash;15 min &middot; highest-value step on this list &mdash; don&rsquo;t skip it</p>
  <ul class="checks">
    <li>You&rsquo;ve watched one person who isn&rsquo;t you try to use the app, without coaching them.</li>
    <li>They got through the main workflow without asking for help.</li>
    <li>You&rsquo;d be comfortable sending this link to a friend today.</li>
    <li>You wouldn&rsquo;t be embarrassed if someone screenshotted the homepage.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="next-block">
    <h3>What to do next</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Fix before you share widely:</strong> broken signup, missing privacy/terms, placeholder text, dev-only buttons visible, seed data exposed, one user seeing another&rsquo;s data.</li>
      <li><strong>Fix soon after launch:</strong> mobile layout quirks, weak link previews, empty screens without guidance, error messages that crash instead of explain.</li>
      <li><strong>More than ~5 serious problems?</strong> Pause the launch push until the worst ones are handled.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <p class="closing">
    Pre-Launch Checklist prepared by LaunchLook &middot;
    <a href="https://launchlook.app">launchlook.app</a>
    {%- if delivered_at %} &middot; {{ delivered_at }}{% endif %}
    <br />
    Free to copy and share. Bundled with every paid LaunchLook tier (Starter, Scale Up, Pro).
  </p>

</body>
</html>
